title: Australia's legal tobacco market could collapse by 2029
description: Australia's legal tobacco market faces potential collapse within three years, with warnings that organised crime-run black markets could take over. The federal government is being urged to review tobacco excise policies and examine whether increased penalties are needed to combat the illegal tobacco trade. #tobacco #federalgovernment

title: Fatal wrong-way crash on Bruce Highway | 7NEWS
description: A fatal head-on collision occurred on the Bruce Highway when three vehicles began travelling in the wrong direction, with a truck colliding with a car carrying a 26-year-old Redcliffe man who died at the scene. The truck driver sustained critical injuries and was hospitalised. Police are investigating why the vehicles were travelling southbound in the northbound lanes around 10:30pm, with the highway closed for approximately six hours. title: Prince Andrew faces police probe over Epstein trafficking claims | 7NEWS
description: Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor is under police investigation following revelations that women were allegedly sex trafficked into the UK via Jeffrey Epstein's private jet, known as the Lolita Express. The aircraft touched down in the UK 90 times, with 15 visits occurring after Epstein's conviction for soliciting underage sex. Newly unredacted emails from 2015 contradict Buckingham Palace's previous denials, with messages suggesting the former prince had consensual sex with Virginia Dufresne when she was 17, and that at least one victim was allegedly brought into Buckingham Palace. title: Perth council under fire for anti-homeless noise devices | 7NEWS
description: The City of Perth has installed high-pitched noise-emitting speakers in a CBD underpass and car parks, which rough sleepers say effectively prevents them from sheltering in these locations. Homelessness advocates have criticised the devices as hostile architecture, while the council maintains they are safety measures, with neither the City nor transport authority taking clear responsibility for the decision. The controversy follows a similar incident in Bunbury in 2023 where a Wiggles song was played on loop to deter homeless people. title: Manhunt underway after Western Sydney drive-by shooting | 7NEWS
description: A drive-by shooting occurred at a Sinclair home on Menzies Circuit in Western Sydney just before 1am, with shots fired into the property narrowly missing a person sleeping inside. A car was subsequently found on fire in neighbouring Colyton, with police treating both incidents as linked. A manhunt is underway across Western Sydney as detectives investigate the connected incidents.
